social_posts.post_text: Prescription drug prices can take a big chunk out of your paycheck and you shouldn’t have to ration lifesaving medication like insulin to pay other bills. Democrats capped insulin at $35/month so cost isn’t a barrier to living a healthy life.

Today the world stands in solidarity to unite in the fight against HIV, to show support for those living with HIV, and to remember those who have died from AIDS.

Thank you to the countless activists and organizations who have never given up in this fight. #WorldAIDSDay

It has been 81 years today since 2,403 sailors, soldiers, and civilians lost their lives at Pearl Harbor. 

On this Pearl Harbor Remembrance Day we remember them and honor their memories. 

#pearlharbor #pearlharborremembranceday
Paul Gosar supports Trump more than our democracy. Example #55.

Republicans continue to show us that they’re out of step with what a majority of Americans want. 

I was proud to vote for marriage equality. @POTUS, let’s get this over the finish line. 

#respectformarriageact #marriageequality

What happened at Sandy Hook still feels unthinkable. Yet the evil that took place, the unfathomable pain, is part of America’s story now. 

The only way forward is to make sure this tragedy finally prompts real progress. It’s our duty to those 26 beautiful kids and educators.

The January 6th Committee shows us just how fragile our democracy is. If this happened once, it could happen again. 

We need to learn lessons from January 6th, but we also have to put those lessons into action. We need to revise our standards and change the way that Congress holds the executive accountable. 

This can never happen again.
Moved by President Zelensky’s speech to Congress last night. He is right: supporting Ukraine isn’t charity. It’s an investment in global security.

In these last few days of 2022, I hope you're doing whatever makes you happy and feeling refreshed. For me, that's spending quality time with Liz, Emmy, and Caroline. 

We're going to have our work cut out for us in 2023, but we'll be ready!
Happy New Year! Guess which one of us made it to midnight.

Emmy accompanied me today at the Capitol as I voted against yet another attempt by House Republicans to attack women’s rights. I hope that in the not so distant future, every kid in America knows what it’s like to once again live in a country that actually respects reproductive rights.

The Ukrainians are fighting for their lives everyday.

The fact that the Speaker of the House would even consider selling Ukraine out by cutting U.S. support in exchange for votes is shameful.

Well we celebrated a couple months late, but I am endlessly grateful to everyone who volunteered for my reelection campaign throughout 2022. 

I can't do any of this without you!
While the shoveling does get old fast, there’s nothing like Salem in the snow

Thank you to the @massdems Veterans and Military Families Subcommittee members for a productive meeting this weekend in Lynn. 

I look forward to partnering as we encourage more veterans to get involved with the Democratic Party across Massachusetts. #mapoli

What we need more of in Washington these days isn’t intelligence. It’s political courage. We need more leaders with the political courage to speak out on important issues even if it’s not politically advantageous, to take that tough vote, to reach across the aisle when progress is the end result.

Happy 2nd Birthday to Caroline— a belated celebration for our Valentine’s Day baby! 

Hope she always looks at me this way (even if many of you have advised the teen years can be a bit… different).

As a Marine veteran, I would not be here in Congress without the GI Bill benefits that I received after returning from Iraq. When I learned of the injustices Black veterans faced after World War II, and how it affects families to this day, I knew it was a moral imperative to work on this bill. Grateful for the partnership of Congressman Clyburn on this hugely important issue.
The Defense Department needs to stop sitting on its hands and implement the Brandon Act.

For those of us who served in Iraq, the legacy of the war is particularly complicated. 

Today, on the 20th anniversary of the start of the war, I'm thinking about all of the men and women I served with. A lot of us disagreed with the war and the decisions being made in Washington...but we went so someone else didn't have to. 

The lessons I learned in Iraq about leadership, integrity, and the importance of finding common ground guide everything I do as a member of Congress.

The reprehensible actions of Tennessee MAGA republicans make it clear that the fight to protect our democracy never ends. I want Emmy and every other kid to know that (14 years from now) her vote will count!  Ill never stop fighting for what’s right.
Happy (belated) Easter from our bunnies to yours!

Had a great time stopping by the @massdems annual Chinatown Banquet last week. I'm always energized by this crowd! 

Thank you to @wutrain, @repmichlewitz, and Chairman Gus Bickford for hosting. Let's keep up the energy and the good work.
Happy birthday to my amazing wife Liz! You make this crazy life we live all possible. I couldn’t imagine a better partner and a more incredible role model for our girls. To many, many more!

A couple weeks ago, I asked the Marine Corps and the Navy to create & prominently display new 9-8-8 posters on bases around the world. 

Spreading the word about mental health resources is critical, especially for our servicemembers.
The best mom I could ask for ❤️
Like a star quarterback, Mom does it all! Thanks for juggling Emmy & Caroline and so much else! We love you so much ❤️
Love these early summer nights in #MA06. Today it’s back to DC for a busy week— let’s hope the Republicans get their act together so we can make it a productive one.
Being a dad is my favorite job. Today I’m looking forward to having a daddy-daughter day with my girls. Happy Father’s Day to all of the dads and father figures out there!
Love is love. Happy #pridemonth from Salem!

Over in Philadelphia, I-95 is already partially reopened less than 2 weeks after the collapse. Yet here in Lynn, the once grand commuter rail station isn't slated to reopen until 2030! This is totally unacceptable for Lynners who rely on the train commute into the city. 

We should have a vision for the future, not this closed down relic of the past.
Extraordinary events playing out in Russia over the last few days. The Putin-Prighozin saga is likely far from over. But right now, the Ukrainians should capitalize on this instability.

Will Rollins isn't afraid to take on the threats facing our country.

After 9/11 he stepped up to take on terrorists as a prosecutor, and in 2022 he took on election denier Ken Calvert and nearly flipped his seat blue.

Serve America and I are proud to endorse @willrollinsca for Congress 🇺🇸

The first year of 988 exceeded my expectations, but there is a lot of work to do to ensure that 100% of calls are answered and that 100% of Americans know about the service and feel empowered to get help when they need it. 

Everyone has a part to play. Help to spread the word by having conversations about mental health with friends and family.

Great turnout for this weekend’s second annual Democracy Summer Food Drive. 

Team Moulton collected over six hundred pounds of food and delivered it to My Brother’s Table in Lynn!
I loved sneaking in some late summer fun with the girls. Back to school in just a few days!
Our animal loving, pancake slinging, math whiz is headed to pre-K! Only a few tears shed this morning… but just by Mom and Dad.

Women who choose to serve their country in the military should NOT be treated like second class citizens. 

Yet Sen. Tuberville is willing to jeopardize our entire military chain of command just to ensure that women don't have the same rights to healthcare as their male counterparts.
The lack of basic political courage in Washington right now is a real problem -- especially when we need to come together to fund the government and avoid a shutdown.
How did I get so lucky? Thank you for all you’ve done for us over the last six exciting and joyous years. Happy anniversary, Liz, I love you!

Thanks to Kowloon and the Wong family @kowloon_restaurant for a great meal tonight.

Emmy declared “This is the best restaurant EVER!”

Great to see Senator Warren this weekend at the Mass Dems convention in Lowell!

We're wondering what kind of chaos the Republicans will cook up this week in Washington...

Donald Trump recently posted on Truth Social that a phone call made by the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff was “an act so egregious that, in times gone by, the punishment would have been DEATH.” 

What an extraordinarily reckless thing to say about our nation's highest-ranking military officer. 

I said it a few days ago and it bears repeating: the Republican party, led by Donald Trump, is a threat to national security.
Long week in Washington trying to stop a shutdown (with no end in sight), but always thinking about these two.
A last minute session week means a few days in DC with Dad. No speaker votes for them, but plenty of museums and exploring.
I don't know much about wrestling, but I've never seen someone win by turning tail and running away…
I’ve got my assistant back in town to help with Speaker votes.
Happy Halloween from spooky Salem! This rainbow princess unicorn and “moo” are ready for some treats👻

The Battle of Fallujah, fought by the Marines almost two decades ago, should offer a key lesson for Israel as it continues its war against Hamas. Just like the Marines shifted their strategy to reduce civilian casualties in Fallujah, Israel must tighten its rules of engagement and make protecting innocent civilians a core strategic objective.  My latest op-ed: https://time.com/6342167/israel-must-learn-from-fallujah/
Special delivery! I hope you’ll donate some holiday cheer to those in need this holiday season — whether it’s gifts from Santa or just your time volunteering in your community.
My second assistant was back on the job today, so I treated her to lunch like any good manager would. Thanks to One Mighty Mill in Lynn for the killer meatball sub and hospitality!
Supporting Ukraine sends a message to autocrats around the world that democracies stick together. And that Putin ultimately won't get away with this criminal war.

This is part of my Letter to the Editor in today's Wall Street Journal, responding to a recent editorial that criticized President Biden for urging Israel to change its military tactics in Gaza. 

We are not pressuring Israel to change tactics to restrain its mission, but to ensure it succeeds at eliminating Hamas and paving the way for a future peace. 

My full response: 
https://www.wsj.com/articles/israel-hamas-president-biden-civilians-gaza-5ba5cc50?mod=letterstoeditor_article_pos1

I’ve always loved the holidays, but watching these two make new memories each year makes it that much more special. I hope everyone had some time to enjoy the season with loved ones. Let’s see what 2024 has in store!

January 6th showed the world that American democracy is resilient – but it is fragile.

I hope this three-year anniversary serves as a stark reminder to every American that we must work together to sideline extremism. 

If we take our democracy for granted again, this time we could lose it.
Father, husband, Marine, Congressman.
